The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | In the City
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                     IN THE CITY
                  
	The CAB on Saturday chalked out plans to improve the game in the districts by 2012. It was decided in a meeting that as part of Mission 2012, several district cricket academies will be launched and facilities will be improved with new exclusive grounds for the game.           
	 Akhtar Ali reached the finals of the senior doubles (over-65) with C.B. Raju after beating C. Radhakrishna and V.R. Kulkarni 6-4, 3-6, 7-5 at the 2nd GVK-AISTA Senior National Ranking Tennis meet in South Club.          
	FOOTBALL: Mohun Bagan vs Mohammedan Sporting at the Salt Lake Stadium      
	TENNIS: GVK-AISTA meet at South Club       
	SNOOKER: BRC championship at the Bengal Rowing Club.                                                                                                                                                                     
